        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Sept 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Günther</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Your answers to all my many queries are so full, clear &amp; explicit that I have not a word more to ask, &amp; they will be of the <hi rend="underline">greatest</hi> use to me.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I would not on any account ask you to write to America about which sex of the Chromids sits on the nest; but <hi rend="underline">if you write on any other subject</hi>, I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be very much obliged if you would ask.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I am delighted to hear that M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Ford will undertake the drawings. I had forgotten about differences of size in sexes; no doubt the female must be in due proportion smaller.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>Any species of Salmon, which presents during the breeding season the difference in jaws will do very well.—<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
<p>Will you ask M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Ford whether he has done the drawings of the feather of Polyplectron &amp; Peacock.— I hope so, otherwise I shall have a terrible hunt to get out the specimens again.—<ref target="#foot.f6"/></p>
<p>With the most cordial thanks &amp; sincere sympathy | Your’s very truly | Ch. Darwin</p>
<p>P.S. | <hi rend="underline">Private</hi> | I wish you had told me some news about your child, &amp; how you succeed.<ref target="#foot.f7"/> You have indeed had a hard &amp; cruel lot to bear.—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Beckenham] <hi rend="italic">before del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Bromley.</hi>’ </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
